<Author>shadowVirginia
<Content>Make sure you stay here !! My husband and I thoroughly enjoyed Villa Carlotta. The staff were so welcoming and helpful (sold stamps and made sure that mail was posted). Our room was immaculate and furnished with wonderful antiques. There is a nice patio with a fountain for personal picnics; there is a nicely appointed bar area. The staff will help you with access to the internet. Their breakfast is incredible ! Access to the bus is within easy walking distance. If you are interested in more long distance yet achievable walking, you can walk to Piazza Michelangelo as well as downtown Florence. We will be back ! 
