<Author>JJCG
<Content>Excellent Location Villa Carlotta is in a beautiful setting near the Pitti Palace. It is approximately a 20 minute walk to the main sites in Florence center. The walk is very pleasant and through fabulous, non-touristy streets with great shops and restaurants. The hotel itself sits in a neighborhood filled with green trees, lush plants, and gorgous, private palazzos. The hotel's parking is safe and immediately behind the hotel. We stayed 2 nights with our 5 month old daughter. The hotel provided a cot for her to sleep in. Further, they provided us with room service for dinner. The hotel restaurant is INCREDIBLE -- we would highly recommend eating there. There is also an internet access computer in the lobby for guest use as well as a bar which is always staffed for coffee or any other type of beverage. The room was clean with period pieces, although the bathroom was very small. We would highly recommend it for a stay in Florence if you are interested in not being in the very center of the city and enjoy staying a bit outside of it. 
