<Author>nunununu
<Content>Lovely This is a lovely hotel! Set in the hills above Florence, this is a great little place especially suited for those with a car, as they have a private parking, those who do not mind taking a taxi every day, or those with good strong legs who love to walk.I stayed in the annex which is behind the main house. The room was large by European standards. There was a small TV which I did not care to watch. The honor bar was well-stocked. It was so quiet! Even though my room faced the parking, I did not hear one thing, until my pleasant wake up call in the morning. Because it was so quiet I fell right back asleep and missed breakfast! The bathroom was well appointed, and the heated towel rack was a nice touch after my long bath in the oversized tub.By the time I woke up, it was after checkout and after breakfast. They did not make an issue of my late checkout and they were nice enough to offer me some coffee and some cookies. They could not offer me breakfast as the kitchen was closed, and they seemed upset that they could not accomdate me for my laziness. What service! I was also permitted to wait in the beautiful lounge for my friend to return. She woke up on time and told me the breakfast was lovely. 
