<Content>quiet hotel in Florence We stayed 2 nights here in late September 2003. A good overall experience. Chose it for it's location near the quiet gardens and because of it's free parking because we had a car. The villa is well kept up and lovely. The rooms with perhaps 20 foot ceilings spacious and well kept. Baths nice but not recently renovated. The staff helpful with dinner reservations etc.It is about a 15 minute walk from the Ponte Vecchio so not right in the storico antico but we like to walk and there is a lot of shopping along the way.The bar area is nice, breakfast ample but not extensive. Service in these areas is not their strong point. They have a computer in the bar area free for the use of the guests with high speed access to the internet. They have a restaurant but we didn't try it. 
