<Content>Florence retreat I stayed at the Villa Carlotta in February and was pleased with my choice. Location is key - south of the Arno near the Boboli Gardens and the Institute of Art, Villa Carlotta is one of a number of lovely villas set amidst trees, gardens, and private drives with wrought iron gates. I like to walk, so I visited the sites on foot. Pitti Palace and Boboli Gardens are very close, next closest is Uffizi, then Duomo - Accademia is a bit of a hike.Another plus was free parking (I rented a car for day trips to Deruta, etc.) - parking can be quite expensive in the center of Florence.The room was fine - comfortable and clean. Staff at the front desk was very helpful - offering driving directions and suggestions for activities during my stay.Only negative was that the bar and dining areas were understaffed - would often wait and wait for someone, then end up having to ask at the front desk to. 
